# Nuxt UI dropdown items: use onSelect, not click

Nuxt UI v3 (`@nuxt/ui` 3.x, used with Nuxt 4) changed the dropdown-item action callback from `click` to `onSelect`. Using `click` silently does nothing.

## Rule

When building items for `UDropdownMenu` (or any Nuxt UI menu/dropdown component), always use `onSelect` for the action callback.

```typescript
// BAD — click is silently ignored in Nuxt UI v3
const items = [
  { label: 'Edit', icon: 'i-lucide-pencil', click: () => openEditor() },
]

// GOOD — onSelect is the correct callback
const items = [
  { label: 'Edit', icon: 'i-lucide-pencil', onSelect: () => openEditor() },
]
```

## Applies to

- `UDropdownMenu` `:items` prop
- Any computed/inline array of menu-item objects passed to Nuxt UI dropdown or context-menu components

## Quick check

If you see `click:` inside a menu-item object literal (not a Vue template `@click`), replace it with `onSelect:`.
